+# Local GenEval Reward Server Notes
+
+This checkout is used as the dependency-isolated GenEval path for the image calibration pipeline.
+
+Prepared locally:
+
+```text
+Python env: /home/hal-jundas/codes/UniRL/.envs/reward_server
+Mask2Former checkpoint: evaluations/reward-server/model/mask2former2/mask2former_swin-s-p4-w7-224_lsj_8x2_50e_coco.pth
+mmdetection 2.x config tree: evaluations/reward-server/mmdetection
+Server GPU count: 4 in gunicorn.conf.py
+Torch stack: torch==2.11.0+cu129, torchvision==0.26.0+cu129
+MMCV stack: mmcv-full==1.7.2 built locally with CUDA 12.9, sm_100, GCC 13.3
+MMDetection: mmdet==2.28.2 installed editable from the local checkout
+OpenCV: opencv-python-headless==4.11.0.86
+Reusable wheel: /home/hal-jundas/codes/UniRL/.cache/wheels/mmcv_full-1.7.2-cp310-cp310-linux_aarch64.whl
+```
+
+The upstream install command pins `torch==2.1.2+cu121`, but on this ARM node the CUDA 12.1 PyTorch wheel index only exposes torch versions up to `2.0.1`. This local setup therefore uses the newer CUDA 12.9 PyTorch stack already used by the workspace. The working path is a locally built `mmcv-full==1.7.2` wheel for Python 3.10, CUDA 12.9, and `sm_100`; plain `mmcv==2.x` must not be installed in this environment because it shadows the legacy MMCV exports required by `mmdet==2.28.2`.
+
+The local `reward_server/gen_eval.py` paths have been patched to point at the downloaded Mask2Former checkpoint and the local mmdetection config. Import validation passes for `mmcv`, `mmcv.ops`, `mmdet.apis`, and `reward_server.gen_eval`.
+
+If the MMCV stack needs to be repaired, uninstall both possible package names and reinstall from the local wheel:
+
+```bash
+/home/hal-jundas/codes/UniRL/.envs/reward_server/bin/python -m pip uninstall -y mmcv mmcv-full
+/home/hal-jundas/codes/UniRL/.envs/reward_server/bin/python -m pip install --no-deps /home/hal-jundas/codes/UniRL/.cache/wheels/mmcv_full-1.7.2-cp310-cp310-linux_aarch64.whl
+```
+
+`pip check` reports that `mmengine` wants `opencv-python` and that `nvidia-cusparselt-cu12` is unsupported on this platform. This env intentionally uses `opencv-python-headless` because the regular package fails to import on the login node without `libGL.so.1`. The practical check is importing `cv2`, `mmcv`, `mmdet.apis`, and `reward_server.gen_eval`, which currently passes.
+
+Start the server from this directory inside the existing Slurm allocation only:
+
+```bash
+srun --overlap --jobid=4745 bash -lc 'cd /home/hal-jundas/codes/UniRL/evaluations/reward-server; export MPLCONFIGDIR=/tmp/matplotlib-reward-server; export GENEVAL_DEVICE=cuda; export GENEVAL_NUM_DEVICES=1; /home/hal-jundas/codes/UniRL/.envs/reward_server/bin/gunicorn "app_geneval:create_app()"'
+```
+
+Use `GENEVAL_NUM_DEVICES=1` for smoke tests and raise it to `4` only for larger batches after the single-worker path has loaded and scored successfully.
+
+The calibration pipeline can then call:
+
+```bash
+python experiments/image_calibration/calibration_pipeline.py eval-geneval \
+  --run-dir outputs/image_calibration/<run> \
+  --server-url http://127.0.0.1:18085
+```
+
+As of the latest check, `srun --overlap --jobid=4745 nvidia-smi -L` fails with `Unable to contact slurm controller`; no GPU-backed reward server should be started until overlap access works again.
